               <provenance>The original name of the donor has been
                     washed out and replaced with the name of Takla Hāymānot, written with a thin
                     pen in a secondary hand (the same as Additio 1): 2ra, 4va, 5va, 16rb, 39vb, 47va, 49va, 52ra, 57rb, 62rb, 78va,
                     88ra, 95rb, 96rb, 109rb, 113va, 233rb. Other names are written interlinearly in
                     a different (more recent?) hand, in strong vermilion ink: Gabra Giyorgis
                        (2ra, 3rb, 4va, 5va, 9ra, 9va, 233rb), Takla
                     ʾƎgziʾ (13ra, 16rb), Walatta ʿAbiyä ʾƎgziʾ
                        (21ra), Wäl(dä) Śǝllāse (26vb), Gabra Mikāʾel (35va), Walda
                     Gäbrʾel (39vb), Walatta Gabrǝʾel (47va), Walatta Śǝllāse (53vb), ʿAmda Māryām (57rb), Walatta
                     ʾIyasus (78va), Zämmädä Māryām (95rb), Gabra Masqal (109
                     rb), ʾAqba Mikāʾel (155ra), Fǝqǝrtä Mikāʾel
                        (233rb). Text III mentions ʾAsratä Māryām
                        (234va).</provenance></history>
